<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8516> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8516" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 732" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2639> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2639" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cn. Domitius Ahenobarbus succeeded Q. Fulvius Flaccus. Liv. 42.28.10-13, Oppido adulescens sacerdos." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2557> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2557" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cic. Verr. 2.1.106; Liv. 41.27.1; 43.16.2; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 48f., 123, 458f.; Vell. 1.10.6; Plin. NH 7.157; Fest. 360 L; and on Fulvius, Val. Max. 2.7.5. They expelled nine from the Senate including a brother of Fulvius the Censor (see 180, note 3; Liv. 41.27.2; Val. Max. 2.7.5; Vell. 1.10.6; Frontin. Str. 4.1.32), and degraded many knights. They carried on an extensive program of building in Rome, Fulvius also in Pisaurum, Fundi, Potentia, and Sinuessa (Liv. 41.27.1-2, and 5-13). Fulvius also robbed the temple of Juno Lacinia of its marble tiles for his temple of Fortuna Equestris, but was compelled to return them (Liv. 42.3.1-11; Val. Max. 1.1.20). He dedicated his temple in 173 (Liv. 42.10.5) and Postumius founded the lustrum (42.10.1-4). They chose M. Aemilius Lepidus Princeps Senatus (Liv. 41.27.1). On Postumius, see 180, Consuls; Münzer, APF 213; Lübker no. 3." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2471> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2471" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 40.43.4; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 48f., 122, 456f.; Plin. NH 35.14; Obseq. 7; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; and on Manlius,{392} who was by birth a brother of his colleague, Vell. 2.8.3; Cic. De Or. 2.260. Both Consuls were assigned Liguria (Liv. 40.44.3), where Fulvius transferred many Ligurians away from the mountains. He also prevented settlement in Italy of Transalpine Gauls (40.53.1-6; Flor. 1.19.5), then returned to Rome to celebrate a triumph (Liv. 40.59.1-3; Degrassi 555). Fulfilled a vow of temple and games (40.44.8-12, and 45.6) for his victory in Spain." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2465> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2465" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Q. Fulvius Flaccus succeeded C. Servilius Geminus as pontifex. M. Aemilius Lepidus succeeded C. Servilius Geminus as pontifex maximus. Cf. Val. Max. 6.6.1." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2464> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2464" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 40.42.6 and 11-12." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2455> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2455" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Proconsul (Liv. 40.39.1) in Hither Spain. Requested permission to bring his army home (Liv. 40.35.3-36.13) but was refused. Won a victory over the Celtiberi before returning to celebrate a triumph (Liv. 40.40.15, 43.4-7, and 59.3; 42.34.9; Diod. 29.28; App. Ib. 42). See Degrassi 555." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2420> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2420" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "His imperium prorogued in Hither Spain (Liv. 40.18.6), he won a victory over the Celtiberi (40.30.1-33.9; cf. Diod. 29.28; Frontin. Str. 2.5.8; App. Ib. 42; Oros. 4.20.31, Praetor)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2419> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2419" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Livy strangely applies the term praetor to both Flaccus and Manlius (40.18.6, 32.8, and 34.1). In Frontinus Cimbrico is probably an error for Celtiberico." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2391> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2391" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Made war upon the Celtiberi and captured Urbicna (Liv. 40.16.7-10)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2390> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2390" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Elections: Liv. 39.51.5 Provinces and armies 40.1.1-2 and 4 and 7." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2344> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2344" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "His active campaign for the place of the deceased Praetor Decimius led the Senate to refuse to hold an election rather than allow him to accumulate another curule office (Liv. 39.39.2-15; cf. Mommsen, Str. 1.513f., note 3)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2343> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2343" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Livy (39.39.2) calls Flaccus aedilis curulis designatus. Mommsen (Str. 1.513f., note 3) has shown that he must have been Curule Aedile for this year, and the objection therefore was to the illegal accumulation of two magistracies in one year (which was forbidden long before, Liv. 7.42.2). As a plebeian Flaccus could be Aedile in 184 but not in 183, a patrician year. Decimius died before the Ludi Apollinares (Liv. 39.39.1 and 15), and elections were not held so early at this time. Flaccus moreover campaigned sine toga candida, presumably because he was in office and could not take off the praetexta." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10094> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10094" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Triumph de Liguribus. MRR I.391-2, Itgenshorst no.190, Rich no. 189." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10093> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10093" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Triumph de Celtibereis. MRR I.389, Itgenshorst no. 189, Rich no. 188." .
